-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Miguel A. Ballicora</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i>ORDO v0.9.6 Ratings for chess and other games</i>. September 2014, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&amp;pid=sites&amp;srcid=ZGVmYXVsdGRvbWFpbnxnYXZpb3RhY2hlc3NlbmdpbmV8Z3g6NmQ0NmNhNGM4YjA3YTc5ZQ\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Tony_Marsland\" title=\"Tony Marsland\">Tony Marsland</a> (<b>1992</b>). <i>Computer Chess and Search.</i> Encyclopedia of Artificial Intelligence (2nd ed.) (ed. S.C. Shapiro) pp. 224-241. John Wiley &amp; Sons, Inc., New York, NY. ISBN 0-471-50305-3. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://webdocs.cs.ualberta.ca/~tony/RecentPapers/encyc.mac-1991.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=555522&amp;t=50823\">The texel evaluation function optimization algorithm</a> by <a href=\"/Peter_%C3%96sterlund\" title=\"Peter Österlund\">Peter Österlund</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 31, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/Texel%27s_Tuning_Method\" title=\"Texel&#39;s Tuning Method\">Texel's Tuning Method</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chessdom.com/tcec-computer-chess-live/\">TCEC computer chess LIVE!</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ext